content:
I've added some subgraphs to thegraph.com for some deposit contracts (specifically topaz, onyx and altona).  This allows for external tools to obtain deposit data (I'm using it in `ethereal` to check if there is already a deposit for a given public key, for example).

Usage is pretty painless.  A simple example:

```
$ curl -s --data '{"query": "{deposits(where:{index:\"217\"}){index validatorPubKey amount withdrawalCredentials signature}}"}'   https://api.thegraph.com/subgraphs/name/attestantio/eth2deposits-altona| jq .
{
  "data": {
    "deposits": [
      {
        "amount": "32000000000",
        "index": "217",
        "signature": "0xa0c9fbe39247866ca7ea1e60fbea0e59df81ebab9708b0b00c10a81c7c3607b74dd5be8a726b36e9dc350732941a2cbb0993fc0df63354b8173e3601fd7bae169b95e22a9c467da550bdd542cc1dc9759dcb9a8b78f96037ac6edaff38712d36",
        "validatorPubKey": "0x864c1d93f84ba7fd40a96ce590cafe9320a2495c8678625619268d61cdeb7be6f096d3980b416c5913a2daeb05f9a6d6",
        "withdrawalCredentials": "0x006d88730be93e7bbd894363ae9b5d03a16f0edf4d30d3e969b3efda66f9f3a4"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Change `altona` to `onyx` or `topaz` as you wish.
